# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# AI-Workhorse v8 – Environment Configuration
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# Copy this file to .env and fill in all values marked with CHANGE_ME.
#
# Start (local):  docker compose up -d
# Start (prod):   docker compose --profile prod up -d
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# ─── Authentication ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Bearer token that clients must send as:  Authorization: Bearer <API_KEY>
# Open WebUI uses this as its OPENAI_API_KEY automatically (see docker-compose.yml).
# Leave empty ONLY for local development (auth is then disabled).
API_KEY=CHANGE_ME_STRONG_API_KEY

# ─── AI Provider Keys ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Required: Google Gemini (primary LLM + embeddings)
# Get a free key at https://aistudio.google.com
GEMINI_API_KEY="MY_GEMINI_API_KEY"

# Optional: DeepSeek (reasoning model)
# Get a key at https://platform.deepseek.com
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY="MY_DEEPSEEK_API_KEY"

# Optional: Mistral AI (mistral-large-latest, mistral-small-latest, codestral-latest)
# Get a key at https://console.mistral.ai
MISTRAL_API_KEY="MY_MISTRAL_API_KEY"

# ─── Database (PostgreSQL + pgvector) ─────────────────────────────────────────
POSTGRES_USER=workhorse
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=CHANGE_ME_STRONG_PASSWORD
POSTGRES_DB=workhorse_db
# DATABASE_URL is auto-constructed from above. Override here only if needed:
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://workhorse:password@db:5432/workhorse_db

# ─── Open WebUI ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Secret key for Open WebUI session signing. Change before going to production!
WEBUI_SECRET_KEY=CHANGE_ME_STRONG_SECRET
# Internal API key used by the sync service to call the Open WebUI REST API.
WEBUI_API_KEY="CHANGE_ME_WEBUI_ADMIN_API_KEY"
# Internal URL of the Open WebUI container (used by the FastAPI backend).
WEBUI_INTERNAL_URL="http://ai-workhorse-webui:8080"

# ─── Agent Loop Limits (Blueprint Rule 7) ─────────────────────────────────────
# Maximum tool-call iterations per chat turn (default: 3)
REACTIVE_MAX_ITERATIONS=3
# Maximum iterations for the Phase 2 autonomous goal engine (default: 10)
GOAL_MAX_ITERATIONS=10

# ─── Web-Search Tool (optional) ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# If set, Serper API is used; otherwise DuckDuckGo is the free fallback.
# Get a free key at https://serper.dev
SERPER_API_KEY=

# ─── Frontend (Next.js Dashboard) ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# URL of the FastAPI backend, callable from the browser.
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8000
# URL of the Open WebUI chat interface.
NEXT_PUBLIC_OPEN_WEBUI_URL=http://localhost:3002

# ─── CORS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Comma-separated list of origins allowed to call the FastAPI backend.
CORS_ALLOW_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3002,http://localhost:3001

# ─── Deployment (Hetzner VPS / Production) ────────────────────────────────────
# Domain for automatic HTTPS via Caddy + Let's Encrypt.
# Only required when starting with: docker compose --profile prod up -d
# Example: DOMAIN=chat.example.com
DOMAIN=your-domain.com

# APP_URL: Public URL of this service (used for self-referential links).
APP_URL="MY_APP_URL"
